  "text": "The etcd-io/etcd client implements a sophisticated client-side retry and timeout policy through multiple coordinated components:\n\n## Retry Interceptor\nThe primary retry mechanism is implemented in `client/v3/retry_interceptor.go`, which provides:\n- `unaryClientInterceptor`: Handles retries for unary (non-streaming) gRPC calls with configurable max retries (default 100), exponential backoff with jitter (25ms base, 10% jitter), and special handling for auth token refresh on ErrInvalidAuthToken and ErrAuthOldRevision errors.\n- `streamClientInterceptor`: Handles retries for server-side streaming calls (Watch operations), buffering messages and re-establishing streams on recoverable errors.\n- `serverStreamingRetryingStream`: A gRPC stream wrapper that buffers sent messages and retries receiving operations while preserving the original client stream interface.\n- `waitRetryBackoff`: Manages backoff timing between retry attempts with context-aware deadline handling.\n- `isSafeRetry`: Determines retry safety based on error type and retry policy (repeatable for immutable ops, non-repeatable for mutable ops).\n\n## Retry Policy Classification\nThe `client/v3/retry.go` file defines fine-grained retry policies:\n- `isSafeRetryImmutableRPC`: Allows retries for immutable operations (Get, Lease queries) on Unavailable status codes, stopping on other server errors.\n- `isSafeRetryMutableRPC`: Restricts retries for mutable operations (Put, Delete) to only when no endpoint is available (write-at-most-once semantics).\n- Provides specialized retry clients: `RetryKVClient`, `RetryLeaseClient`, `RetryClusterClient`, `RetryMaintenanceClient`, `RetryAuthClient` that apply the appropriate policy to each operation.\n\n## Endpoint Balancer and Health Check\nThe endpoint balancer is implemented in `client/v3/internal/resolver/resolver.go`:\n- `EtcdManualResolver`: A gRPC resolver that maintains a list of endpoints with round-robin load balancing policy (configured via service config).\n- Updates endpoints dynamically via `SetEndpoints()` and distributes requests across active endpoints.\n- The `Build()` method configures round-robin load balancing with automatic failover.\n\nConnection health checking occurs in `client/v3/client.go`:\n- `waitForConnection`: Performs gRPC health checks (using gRPC Health Checking Protocol) before considering a connection ready, verifying the endpoint is responsive.\n- Uses `DialTimeout` configuration to bound the health check duration.\n- Gracefully handles Unimplemented and FailedPrecondition responses from servers not supporting health checks.\n\n## Request Timeout Enforcement\nTimeout handling is integrated across multiple layers:\n\n1. **Dial Timeout** (`client/v3/client.go`):\n   - `dialSetupOpts`: Configures the gRPC client with the retry interceptors and timeout policies during connection setup.\n   - `newClient`: Applies DialTimeout (default behavior calls `waitForConnection` with DialTimeout context).\n   - Enforces timeout for initial connection establishment.\n\n2. **KV Operations** (`client/v3/kv.go`):\n   - `NewKV`: Creates KV client wrapping `RetryKVClient` with the client's call options.\n   - `Put`, `Get`, `Delete`, `Do`: All pass context through to gRPC calls, which enforce caller-provided context timeouts via `context.WithTimeout()`.\n   - Errors are processed through `ContextError()` to convert context deadline exceeded errors appropriately.\n\n3. **Watch Operations** (`client/v3/watch.go`):\n   - `NewWatcher`: Creates watch client with call options from the parent client.\n   - `Watch`: Establishes a `watchGRPCStream` that maintains internal stream context with `context.WithCancel()` (never closes on user timeout, allowing reconnection).\n   - Uses special `valCtx` context that never expires internally but respects user context cancellation for shutdown.\n\n4. **Lease Operations** (`client/v3/lease.go`):\n   - `NewLease`: Creates lease client with `firstKeepAliveTimeout` set to `DialTimeout + 1 second` for initial keepalive deadline.\n   - `Grant`, `Revoke`, `TimeToLive`, `Leases`: Pass context directly to `RetryLeaseClient` calls.\n   - `KeepAlive`: Runs indefinite loop handling keep-alive messages with dynamic deadline tracking.\n   - `KeepAliveOnce`: Renews lease with caller-provided context timeout.\n\n5. **Context Error Conversion** (`client/v3/client.go`):\n   - `ContextError()`: Converts gRPC DeadlineExceeded and Canceled errors to the underlying context error if the context has actually expired/canceled, enabling proper timeout semantics.\n   - Used by all KV, Watch, and Lease operations to report accurate timeout/cancellation information.\n\n## Configuration\nTimeout and retry behavior is configured through:\n- `client/v3/config.go`: Defines `Config` struct with `DialTimeout`, `MaxUnaryRetries`, `BackoffWaitBetween`, `BackoffJitterFraction` fields.\n- `client/v3/options.go`: Defines defaults (`defaultUnaryMaxRetries = 100`, `defaultBackoffWaitBetween = 25ms`, `defaultBackoffJitterFraction = 0.10`).\n- `client/v3/client.go`: Applies these settings during client initialization in `dialSetupOpts()` via the retry interceptor configuration.\n\n## Backoff Strategy\nThe `roundRobinQuorumBackoff()` in `client/v3/client.go` implements intelligent backoff:\n- Calculates backoff duration based on endpoint count and quorum size.\n- Ensures retries are distributed across the cluster endpoints to improve recovery speed.\n- Uses linear backoff with jitter to prevent thundering herd during cluster recovery.\n\nThis comprehensive architecture ensures reliable client-server communication through coordinated retry logic, health checking, endpoint balancing, and proper timeout enforcement across all operation types (KV, Watch, Lease)."
}

